msContents.summary: Includes: a calendar of saints (leaves 1r-6v); Quindecim orationes (7r-20r); Hore beate Marie virginis secundum usum Sarum (21r-74v); Vigilie mortuorum, or, Office of the Dead (leaves 75r-91r); Commendaciones animarum (leaves 93r-102v); Psalterium de passione domini (leaves 103r-107v); Psalterium beati Iheronimi (108r-116v). Also, genealogical notes about Thomas Wakefeld, 1st Regius Professor of Hebrew at Cambridge on first two unnumbered leaves, and Wakefeld's genealogical additions to the calendar.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 23 long lines (dimensions of written space: 116 x 76 mm); frame ruled in ink.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in high grade Gothic Book-hand.

binding.p: Bound in modern pigskin (de Ricci); spine title: Horae B.V.M. Sarum; red and blue marbled edges.

origin.p: Northern Europe (Ghent, Flanders according to de Ricci; France, possibly Rouen according to Pen's excellencie; N. German or Netherlands provenance according to Hecksher on catalog card); ca. 1500

history.provenance: Formerly owned by Thomas Wakefeld (see leaves [2v-3r]); Scott of Harden (bookplate); Boies Penrose II (bookplate); A.J.V. Radford; and Sir Leicester Harmsworth.
